include partials/head.jade
include partials/header.jade
include partials/connect.jade
include partials/footer.jade

-var page = "Education"

doctype html5
html
  head
    +head(page)
  body
    +header(loggedIn, page)
    div.page-wrapper

      div.splash
        h1 Learn & Teach Code
        p Computational skills for researchers



      div.pure-u-1
        div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2.spaced-columns
          div.header-img
          h3 DO YOU WANT TO TEACH?
          p We want help the community learns skills to further open practices in research. To help with this, we've developed both trainings and resources around open research practices.
          ul
            li
              | Want to teach? We run a free online training course for people who want to pass their skills along --- see
              a(href="http://teaching.software-carpentry.org/")  http://teaching.software-carpentry.org/
              |  for more information.
            li Help us create resources (from curricula to broader resources about open science work). All our materials are freely available under open licenses, and contributions are always welcome. Some of our ongoing projects:
              ul
                li
                  | We're composing some lessons on
                  a(href="https://github.com/mozillascience/codeReview")  Code Review
                  |  specially aimed at scientists - learn what makes good code, and how to keep your software projects healthy and growing.
                li
                  | We're building
                  a(href="https://github.com/mozillascience/instructorTraining")  Instructor Training
                  |  content for delivery to a wider audience. Explore our take on educational psychology and teaching skills here.
          span.pure-button Sign Up for Instructor Training


        div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-2.spaced-columns
          div.header-img
          h3 DO YOU WANT TO LEARN?
          p To help people understand what the open web can do to accelerate science, we run workshops all over the world to help scientists learn the skills needed to use today's tools and create tomorrow's. We also will be building out resources for those looking to learn more about the latest tools and policies and how to apply them to their work.
            ul
              li
                | Join a workshop: see
                a(href="http://software-carpentry.org/")  http://software-carpentry.org
                |  for a list of upcoming events, or
                a(href="http://software-carpentry.org/workshops/request.html")  fill out this form
                |  if you'd like Software Carpentry to run one for you.
          span.pure-button Request a Workshop

        div.pure-u-1
          h3 PROGRAMS
          p There are many groups interested in teaching open science skills or the web. Here are a few:
          ul
            li
              a(href="http://altbibl.io/dst4l/") Data Science Training for Libraries / DST4L
            li
              a(href="http://opensciencetraining.com/") Open Science Training Initiative
            li
              a(href="http://ropensci.org/") rOpenSci
            li
              a(href="http://datacarpentry.org/") Data Carpentry
            li
              a(href="https://webmaker.org/make-your-own") Webmaker Teach Templates
            li
              a(href="http://schoolofdata.org/") School of Data
              |  /
              a(href="https://okfn.org/")  Open Knowledge Foundation
            li
              a(href="https://training.github.com/") GitHub training
            li
              a(href="http://schoolofopen.p2pu.org/") Creative Commons / P2PU / School of Open's Open Science Course
            li
              a(href="http://www.pyladies.com/") PyLadies

        div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-3-4.spaced-columns
          h3 CONTACT US
          p Are you running a program to teach software and open science skills to researchers? Is there a set of lessons or discussions that you would like to see built? Let us know in the Mozilla Science Forum under Training, or join the conversation on twitter @MozillaScience.
        div.pure-u-1.pure-u-md-1-4.spaced-columns
          h3
          +connect()


    +footer()

